n%20the%20good%2C%20fair%2C%20or%20poor%20range.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20Fed%20lowers%20interest%20rates%20as%20anticipated%2C%20you%20can%20expect%20personal%20loan%20interest%20rates%20to%20drop%20slightly%2C%20regardless%20of%20your%20credit%20score.%20But%20don't%20expect%20big%20dips%3A%20The%20anticipated%20cut%20is%2025%20to%2050%20basis%20points%20at%20most%2C%20which%20is%20just%200.25%25%20or%200.5%25%2C%20which%20is%20negligible%20in%20the%20grand%20scheme%20of%20compounding%20interest.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPrioritize%20paying%20off%20debt%20(even%20before%20investing)%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20are%20struggling%20with%20paying%20off%20debt%2C%20the%20way%20to%20get%20out%20is%20to%20pay%20off%20the%20principal%20as%20quickly%20as%20possible%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jeremy%20Schneider%2C%20a%20personal%20finance%20educator%20who%20co-founded%20flat-fee%20financial%20advice%20marketplace%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhellonectarine.com%2F%5C%22%3ENectarine%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BGetting%20out%20of%20debt%20is%20really%20about%20making%20a%20plan%20and%20staying%20focused.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchneider%20recommends%20the%20%26quot%3Bsnowball%26quot%3B%20method%20for%20getting%20out%20of%20debt.%20%26quot%3BSort%20all%20your%20debts%20from%20smallest%20to%20largest%2C%20make%20minimum%20payments%20on%20everything%20except%20the%20smallest%2C%20and%20throw%20all%20the%20cash%20you%20can%20at%20the%20smallest%20debt%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BOnce%20that%20is%20paid%20off%2C%20you%20have%20one%20fewer%20payment%20to%20make%2C%20which%20can%20be%20applied%20to%20the%20next%20smallest%20debt%20and%20down%20the%20line.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchneider%20also%20cautioned%20against%20relying%20on%20lower-interest%20financial%20tools%20to%20solve%20the%20problem%3A%20%26quot%3BA%20consolidation%20loan%20won't%20save%20you%20from%20your%20debt%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20pushing