visit%20to%20Singapore%20and%20Brunei%20in%20early%20September%2C%20External%20Affairs%20Minister%20Jaishankar's%20articulation%20of%20India's%20stance%20on%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%2C%20and%20the%20visits%20of%20Vietnamese%20and%20Malaysian%20Prime%20Ministers%20to%20India%2C%20signal%20a%20continuity%20in%20the%20strategic%20significance%20of%20Southeast%20Asia%20to%20India's%20foreign%20policy%20vision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Look%20East'%20To%20'Act%20East'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20central%20government's%20%26quot%3BAct%20East%20Policy%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20evolution%20from%20the%20previous%20%26quot%3BLook%20East%20Policy%2C%26quot%3B%20signifies%20a%20more%20proactive%20engagement%20with%20Southeast%20Asian%20nations.%20Under%20Modi%2C%20this%20policy%20has%20become%20a%20cornerstone%20of%20India's%20Indo-Pacific%20strategy%2C%20which%20promotes%20a%20free%2C%20open%2C%20inclusive%2C%20and%20rules-based%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20region's%20strategic%20importance%20is%20underscored%20by%20its%20geographical%20proximity%20to%20India%20and%20its%20role%20as%20a%20gateway%20to%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%2C%20a%20vital%20maritime%20corridor%20for%20global%20trade.%20Southeast%20Asia%20is%20a%20crucial%20part%20of%20the%20Indo-Pacific's%20geopolitical%20framework%2C%20and%20India's%20growing%20relationship%20with%20the%20region%20is%20seen%20as%20a%20counterbalance%20to%20China's%20expanding%20and%20often%20predatory%20influence.%20In%20Modi%203.0%2C%20India%20aims%20to%20solidify%20its%20position%20as%20a%20reliable%20partner%20in%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20region%2C%20with%20Southeast%20Asia%20being%20a%20crucial%20element%20of%20this%20strategy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENew%20Delhi%20has%20placed%20particular%20emphasis%20on%20fostering%20closer%20ties%20with%20ASEAN%20(Association%20of%20Southeast%20Asian%20Nations)%20member%20states.%20Trade%20between%20India%20and%20ASEAN%20has%20grown%20steadily%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20with%20bilateral%20trade%20exceeding%20%24100%20billion%20in%202023.%20In%20addition%20to%20economic%20cooperation%2C%20India's%20strategic%20interests%20in%20the%20region%20have%20also%20deepened.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESingapore%2C%20Brunei%2C%20Vietnam%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Singapore%2C%20Modi's%20talks%20with%20newly%20elected%20Prime%20Minister%20Lawrence%20Wong%20resulted%20in%20substantive%20agreements%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20semiconductor%20sector%20in%20addition%20to%20health%2C%20skilling%2C%20and%20digital%20security.%20The%20%26quot%3BIndia-Singapore%20Semiconductor%20Ecosystem%20Partnership%26quot%3B%20inked%20during%20the%20visit%2C%20aims%20to%20facilitate%20the%20entry%20of%20Singaporean%20companies%20into%20India.%20This%20partnership%20is%20integral%20to%20New%20Delhi's%20ambitions%20to%20become%20a%20global%20semiconductor%20hub%2C%20leveraging%20complementary%20strengths%20to%20build%20resilience%20in%20the%20global%20chip%20supply%20chain.%20Parallelly%2C%20Modi's%20visit%20to%20Brunei%2C%20a%20strategically%20located%20nation%20in%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%2C%20marked%20a%20key%20moment%20in%20India's%20Act%20East%20Policy%20and%20Indo-Pacific%20vision.%20It%20was%20the%20first%20visit%20by%20an%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20and%20coincided%20with%20the%2040th%20anniversary%20of%20diplomatic%20relations%20between%20the%20two%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Modi%203.0%2C%20Vietnam%20has%20emerged%20as%20one%20of%20India's%20most%20important%20Southeast%20Asian%20partners.%20The%20two%20countries%20share%20concerns%20over%20China's%20growing%20assertiveness%20in%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%2C%20where%20both%20India%20and%20Vietnam%20have%20vested%20interests%20in%20oil%20exploration%20and%20freedom%20of%20navigation.%20Discussions%20on%20defence%20cooperation%2C%20trade%2C%20and%20energy%20security%20marked%20the%20visit%20of%20Vietnamese%20Prime%20Minister%20Ph%E1%BA%A1m%20Minh%20Ch%C3%ADnh%20to%20India.%20Vietnam%20is%20a%20linchpin%20in%20India's%20Act%20East%20Policy%20and%20Indo-Pacific%20strategy%2C%20strengthening%20their%20naval%20ties%20and%20defence%20collaboration.%20India%20and%20Vietnam%20have%20signed%20several%20agreements%20on%20defence%2C%20maritime%20security%2C%20and%20energy%20and%20economic%20cooperation.%20Both%20countries%20are%20committed%20to%20upholding%20international%20law%20in%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%2C%20further%20aligning%20their%20strategic%20interests.%20The%20bilateral%20relationship%20has%20also%20expanded%20into%20renewable%20energy%2C%20IT%2C%20and%20infrastructure%20development%2C%20with%20India%20playing%20a%20significant%20role%20in%20Vietnam's%20development%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EResetting%20Ties%20With%20Malaysia%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20the%20visit%20of%20Malaysian%20Prime%20Minister%20Anwar%20Ibrahim%20to%20India%20highlighted%20a%20much-needed%20reset%20in%20bilateral%20ties%20following%20a%20dip%20in%20relations%20before%202022.%20Malaysia's%20importance%20to%20India%20stems%20from%20its%20strategic%20location%20along%20vital%20maritime%20routes%20in%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20and%20its%20role%20as%20a%20significant%20trading%20partner.%20During%20Anwar's%20visit%2C%20the%20two%20leaders%20discussed%20enhancing%20economic%20cooperation%2C%20particularly%20in%20technology%2C%20renewable%20energy%2C%20and%20digital%20connectivity.%20Malaysia's%20support%20for%20India's%20Act%20East%20Policy%20and%20its%20role%20in%20ASEAN%20make%20it%20a%20valuable%20partner%20for%20India%20as%20it%20seeks%20to%20expand%20its%20presence%20in%20Southeast%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20South%20China%20Sea%20Question%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20India's%20position%20on%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%20has%20evolved%20significantly%20over%20the%20years%2C%20shifting%20from%20a%20cautious%2C%20neutral%20stance%20to%20one%20that%20has%20now%20clearly%20articulated%20its%20support%20for%20the%20Philippines'%20sovereign%20maritime%20territorial%20claims%2C%20freedom%20of%20navigation%20and%20maritime%20resource%20exploitation%2C%20in%20line%20with%20international%20law.%20This%20aligns%20India%20with%20Southeast%20Asian%20nations%20against%20unilateral%20actions%20by%20China%2C%20while%20also%20serving%20India's%20strategic%20interests%20by%20ensuring%20freedom%20of%20navigation%20and%20bolstering%20regional%20security.%20India's%20nuanced%20stance%2C%20informed%20by%20its%20own%20territorial%20tensions%20with%20China%20on%20its%20northern%20land%20border%2C%20underscores%20its%20intent%20to%20deter%20unilateral%20and%20unlawful%20advances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModi%203.0%20marks%20a%20significant%20evolution%20in%20India's%20engagement%20with%20Southeast%20Asia%2C%20driven%20by%20geopolitical%20imperatives%20and%20economic%20interests.%20The%20Modi%20administration%20has%20steadily%20deepened%20the%20extent%20and%20scope%20of%20its%20ties%20with%20Southeast%20Asian%20countries%2C%20and%20his%20third%20consecutive%20tenure%20in%20office%20looks%20poised%20to%20build%20on%20the%20gains%20of%20the%20last%20ten%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Harsh%20V.%20Pant%20is%20Vice%20President%20%E2%80%93%20Studies%20and%20Foreign%20Policy%2C%20at%20Observer%20Research%20Foundation%2C%20and%20Professor%20of%20International%20Relations%20at%20King's%20College%20London.%20Pratnashree%20Basu%20is%20an%20Associate%20Fellow%20-%20Indo-Pacific%2C%20at%20Observer%20Research%20Foundation.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726300080000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2Fi6ubmn8g_modi-malaysia-pm_625x300_20_August_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fmodi-3-0-is-leaving-nothing-to-chance-with-southeast-asia-6563216%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Modi%203.0%20marks