20Department%2C%20must%20mandate%20a%20thorough%20site%20inspection%20before%20granting%20permissions%20for%20the%20construction%20of%20new%20borewells%20or%20septic%20tanks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Metering%20of%20groundwater%20usage%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20installation%20of%20water%20meters%20should%20be%20made%20compulsory%20for%20all%20groundwater%20extraction%20points.%20This%20will%20help%20monitor%20and%20regulate%20groundwater%20usage%2C%20ensuring%20that%20extraction%20remains%20within%20sustainable%20limits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Pricing%20of%20groundwater%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Introduce%20a%20pricing%20mechanism%20for%20groundwater%20usage%20to%20discourage%20excessive%20extraction%20and%20promote%20conservation.%20This%20can%20be%20in%20the%20form%20of%20a%20groundwater%20tax%20or%20a%20tiered%20pricing%20system%20based%20on%20consumption%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Zoning%20regulations%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Implement%20strict%20zoning%20regulations%20to%20control%20the%20density%20of%20borewells%20and%20prevent%20over-extraction%20in%20critical%20groundwater%20recharge%20areas.%20This%20may%20involve%20establishing%20%E2%80%98no-go%E2%80%99%20zones%20where%20groundwater%20extraction%20is%20prohibited%20or%20restricted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Strict%20enforcement%20of%20waste%20disposal%20regulations%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EImplement%20stringent%20regulations%20on%20the%20disposal%20of%20solid%20waste%2C%20sewage%2C%20and%20industrial%20effluents%20to%20prevent%20contamination%20of%20groundwater.%20This%20should%20include%20mandatory%20treatment%20of%20waste%20before%20disposal%2C%20regular%20monitoring%20of%20disposal%20sites%2C%20and%20hefty%20fines%20for%20hotels%20and%20other%20businesses%20found%20dumping%20waste%20%E2%80%94%20including%20expired%20cement%20into%20water%20bodies.%20Moreover%2C%20clear%20guidelines%20must%20be%20set%20on%20the%20minimum%20distance%20that%20must%20be%20maintained%